        bodyEn: '''From Ymir's flesh the gods formed the earth (Midgard), from his blood the seas and oceans, from his bones the mountains, from his teeth the rocks and pebbles, and from his hair the trees. The giant's skull was raised to become the dome of the sky, held up by four dwarves named Nordri, Sudri, Austri, and Vestri at the four cardinal points. His brains were flung into the air to become clouds. The gods caught sparks from Muspelheim to make the sun, moon, and stars, then fixed their courses to govern day, night, and the seasons. From Ymir's eyebrows they built the stronghold of Midgard to shield humankind from the giants. Finally, from the maggots gnawing at Ymir's flesh, the gods created the race of dwarves who dwell beneath the earth.''',
