        body: '''Dalam kosmos Nordic terdapat dua keluarga dewa yang berbeda. Aesir, yang bersemayam di Asgard, adalah dewa-dewa perang, kekuasaan, dan tatanan, dipimpin Odin sang Bapak Semua bersama Thor dan Tyr. Sementara itu Vanir mendiami Vanaheim dan merupakan dewa kesuburan, kemakmuran, laut, serta sihir ramalan, dengan tokoh utama Njord serta anak kembarnya Freyr dan Freyja. Kedua bangsa mewakili nilai yang berlainan: Aesir menekankan kekuatan dan hukum, Vanir menekankan kelimpahan dan magi seidr. Untuk waktu yang lama keduanya hidup terpisah tanpa banyak bersinggungan, sampai kedatangan seorang penyihir misterius mengusik hubungan mereka dan menyulut permusuhan pertama yang pernah dikenal dunia.''',
        bodyEn: '''In the Nordic cosmos there were two distinct families of gods. The Aesir, who dwelt in Asgard, were gods of war, sovereignty, and order, led by Odin the All-Father alongside Thor and Tyr. The Vanir, meanwhile, inhabited Vanaheim and were gods of fertility, prosperity, the sea, and prophetic magic, with Njord and his twin children Freyr and Freyja as their chief figures. The two races represented differing values: the Aesir stressed strength and law, the Vanir abundance and seidr magic. For a long time they lived apart with little contact, until the arrival of a mysterious sorceress disturbed their relations and kindled the first enmity the world had ever known.''',
