        bodyEn: '''After the exchange of hostages, the two families of gods merged into a single harmonious pantheon, and from then on the term "Aesir" was often used for all the gods. Njord, Freyr, and Freyja were fully received in Asgard; Freyr became lord of Alfheim and god of the harvest, while Freyja taught the art of seidr magic to the Aesir, including to Odin himself. This union enriched the world of the gods by blending the powers of war and fertility, law and magic. The Aesir–Vanir War became the first and last conflict among the families of gods; afterward they faced a common enemy, the giants. The peace forged endured to the end of days, though seeds of other tragedies, such as the killing of Kvasir by dwarves, would later grow from these events.''',
