      'Odin menyerahkan sebelah matanya sebagai gadai dan meminum air sumur.',
      'Menjadi dewa terbijak, ia mengajarkan rune dan bersiap menghadapi Ragnarok.',
    ],
    chronologyEn: [
      'Odin longed for the secret of the runes carved on Yggdrasil\'s roots.',
      'He pierced himself with the spear Gungnir and hung upon the world tree.',
      'For nine nights he hung without food or drink, offering himself to himself.',
      'On the ninth night, the runes revealed themselves from the depths of the well of fate.',
      'Odin seized the runes and mastered nine songs and eighteen charms.',
      'He came to Mimir\'s well to beg for deeper wisdom.',
      'Odin surrendered one eye as a pledge and drank the well\'s water.',
      'Becoming the wisest god, he taught the runes and prepared for Ragnarok.',
    ],
    impact:
        '''Pengorbanan Odin menjadikannya dewa kebijaksanaan tertinggi dan sumber seluruh pengetahuan rune di dunia Nordic. Rune yang ia rebut menjadi dasar sihir, ramalan, penyembuhan, dan penulisan yang menyebar kepada dewa dan manusia. Matanya di sumur Mimir memberinya penglihatan batin yang menembus takdir, termasuk visi akan Ragnarok. Kesadaran ini mendorong Odin mengumpulkan pahlawan gugur di Valhalla dan mencari pengetahuan tanpa henti melalui gagak Huginn dan Muninn. Sosok Odin bermata satu dengan tombak Gungnir menjadi citra dewa Nordic yang paling ikonik, perlambang harga mahal dari kearifan sejati.''',
    impactEn:
        '''Odin's sacrifice made him the supreme god of wisdom and the source of all rune-knowledge in the Nordic world. The runes he seized became the foundation of magic, prophecy, healing, and writing that spread to gods and humans. His eye in Mimir's well gave him an inner sight that pierced fate, including the vision of Ragnarok. This awareness drove Odin to gather fallen heroes in Valhalla and to seek knowledge ceaselessly through his ravens Huginn and Muninn. The figure of one-eyed Odin with the spear Gungnir became the most iconic image of a Nordic god, a symbol of the steep price of true wisdom.''',
    meaning:
        '''Kisah ini melambangkan gagasan mendalam bahwa kebijaksanaan sejati menuntut pengorbanan dan penderitaan. Odin yang menggantung diri, tertusuk dan terluka demi pengetahuan, sering dibandingkan dengan pola pengorbanan diri dalam berbagai tradisi spiritual dunia. Menyerahkan sebelah mata untuk melihat lebih dalam mengajarkan bahwa untuk memperoleh penglihatan batin, seseorang harus rela kehilangan sesuatu dari penglihatan lahiriah. Rune sebagai bahasa takdir menegaskan keyakinan Nordic akan kuasa kata dan simbol untuk membentuk kenyataan. Odin menjadi teladan pencari kebenaran yang tak kenal takut, yang memandang pengetahuan lebih berharga daripada kenyamanan atau bahkan keutuhan diri.''',
    meaningEn:
        '''This tale symbolizes the profound idea that true wisdom demands sacrifice and suffering. Odin hanging himself, pierced and wounded for knowledge, is often compared to patterns of self-sacrifice in various spiritual traditions around the world. Surrendering one eye to see more deeply teaches that to gain inner sight, one must be willing to lose something of outer vision. The runes as the language of fate affirm the Nordic belief in the power of word and symbol to shape reality. Odin becomes the model of the fearless seeker of truth, who regarded knowledge as more precious than comfort or even his own wholeness.''',
  ),
  MythStory(
    id: 'norse-thor-thrym',
    mythology: 'Nordic',
    icon: '🔨',
    imageUrl: 'assets/images/Nordik/History/hammer.webp',
    title: 'Thor Kehilangan Palunya',
    titleEn: 'Thor\'s Stolen Hammer',
    summary:
        'Raksasa Thrym mencuri palu Mjolnir milik Thor dan menuntut dewi Freyja sebagai tebusan; Thor menyamar sebagai pengantin perempuan untuk merebutnya kembali.',
    summaryEn:
        'The giant Thrym steals Thor\'s hammer Mjolnir and demands the goddess Freyja as ransom; Thor disguises himself as the bride to win it back.',
    timeline: 'Zaman Mitos · Thrymskvida',
    timelineEn: 'Mythic Age · The Lay of Thrym',
    chapters: [
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Latar Belakang: Palu yang Lenyap',
        headingEn: 'Background: The Vanished Hammer',
        body: '''Mjolnir, palu sakti milik Thor, adalah senjata terpenting bagi para dewa Asgard. Ditempa oleh kurcaci, palu itu selalu mengenai sasaran, kembali sendiri ke tangan pemiliknya, dan mampu menumpas raksasa mana pun. Selama Mjolnir berada di tangan Thor, bangsa raksasa tak berani menyerbu Asgard, sebab palu itulah tameng utama yang menjaga keseimbangan antara dunia dewa dan dunia jotun. Suatu pagi Thor terbangun dan mendapati palunya lenyap tanpa jejak. Ia mengibas-ngibaskan janggutnya dan meraba-raba dengan panik, namun Mjolnir benar-benar hilang. Kehilangan ini bukan sekadar musibah pribadi, melainkan ancaman genting bagi seluruh Asgard, karena tanpa palu itu para dewa menjadi rentan terhadap serbuan musuh-musuh raksasa mereka.''',
        bodyEn: '''Mjolnir, Thor's mighty hammer, was the most important weapon of the gods of Asgard. Forged by dwarves, the hammer always struck its mark, returned by itself to its owner's hand, and could crush any giant. As long as Mjolnir remained in Thor's grasp, the giants dared not storm Asgard, for the hammer was the chief shield guarding the balance between the world of gods and the world of the jotun. One morning Thor awoke to find his hammer gone without a trace. He shook his beard and groped about in panic, but Mjolnir was truly lost. This loss was no mere personal misfortune but a dire threat to all of Asgard, for without the hammer the gods became vulnerable to the assault of their giant foes.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Tuntutan Thrym',
        headingEn: 'Thrym\'s Demand',
        body: '''Thor segera mendatangi Loki dan menceritakan hilangnya Mjolnir. Loki meminjam jubah bulu elang milik Freyja agar dapat terbang mencari sang palu. Ia melesat ke Jotunheim dan di sana menemukan pelakunya: Thrym, raja para raksasa. Dengan bangga Thrym mengaku telah mencuri Mjolnir dan menyembunyikannya delapan mil di bawah tanah, di tempat yang takkan pernah bisa ditemukan siapa pun. Ia menyampaikan syaratnya: palu itu hanya akan dikembalikan bila para dewa menyerahkan Freyja, dewi tercantik di Asgard, untuk menjadi istrinya. Loki terbang pulang membawa kabar buruk ini. Ketika Freyja diberitahu bahwa ia harus dinikahkan dengan raksasa, ia begitu murka hingga kalung Brisingamen yang termasyhur terlepas dari lehernya, dan ia dengan tegas menolak menjadi tebusan bagi bangsa jotun.''',
        bodyEn: '''Thor at once went to Loki and told him of Mjolnir's disappearance. Loki borrowed Freyja's falcon-feather cloak so he could fly in search of the hammer. He sped to Jotunheim and there found the culprit: Thrym, king of the giants. Proudly Thrym confessed that he had stolen Mjolnir and hidden it eight miles beneath the earth, in a place no one could ever find. He stated his terms: the hammer would be returned only if the gods handed over Freyja, the fairest goddess in Asgard, to become his wife. Loki flew home bearing this ill news. When Freyja was told she must be wed to a giant, she grew so furious that her famous necklace Brisingamen snapped from her neck, and she firmly refused to be a ransom for the jotun race.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Siasat Sang Pengantin',
        headingEn: 'The Scheme of the Bride',
        body: '''Para dewa berkumpul dalam sidang untuk mencari jalan keluar. Heimdall, sang penjaga yang bijak, mengusulkan sebuah siasat berani: Thor sendiri harus menyamar sebagai Freyja dan pergi ke Jotunheim sebagai pengantin palsu. Thor menolak keras, khawatir para dewa akan menganggapnya banci, tetapi Loki mengingatkan bahwa tanpa Mjolnir para raksasa akan segera menguasai Asgard. Akhirnya Thor mengalah. Para dewa mendandaninya dengan gaun pengantin, menutupi wajahnya dengan cadar, mengalungkan Brisingamen di lehernya, dan menggantungkan seikat kunci rumah tangga di pinggangnya sesuai adat. Loki pun ikut menyamar sebagai dayang pengiring. Keduanya lalu menaiki kereta yang ditarik dua kambing jantan Thor, melaju ke Jotunheim dengan gemuruh sampai gunung-gunung berguncang dan bumi terbakar, menuju aula sang raja raksasa.''',
        bodyEn: '''The gods gathered in council to find a way out. Heimdall, the wise watchman, proposed a bold ruse: Thor himself must disguise as Freyja and go to Jotunheim as a false bride. Thor refused fiercely, fearing the gods would think him unmanly, but Loki reminded him that without Mjolnir the giants would soon seize Asgard. At last Thor relented. The gods dressed him in a bridal gown, veiled his face, hung Brisingamen about his neck, and fastened a bunch of household keys at his waist as custom required. Loki too disguised himself as an attending maidservant. The two then mounted the chariot drawn by Thor's two goats and thundered off to Jotunheim so that the mountains shook and the earth burned, heading for the hall of the giant king.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Pesta Pernikahan di Jotunheim',
        headingEn: 'The Wedding Feast in Jotunheim',
        body: '''Thrym menyambut kedatangan "Freyja" dengan penuh sukacita dan menyiapkan pesta megah. Namun sang pengantin bertingkah aneh: dalam jamuan, Thor melahap seekor lembu utuh, delapan ekor ikan salmon, semua hidangan istimewa untuk para wanita, dan meneguk tiga tong penuh mead. Thrym tercengang melihat nafsu makan pengantinnya, tetapi Loki yang cerdik cepat menjelaskan bahwa Freyja tak makan sedikit pun selama delapan malam karena begitu bergairah menanti pernikahannya. Ketika Thrym menyingkap cadar untuk mencium mempelainya, ia terperanjat oleh sepasang mata yang menyala berapi-api, dan mundur ketakutan. Sekali lagi Loki berdalih bahwa Freyja tak tidur selama delapan malam karena hasratnya yang menggebu, sehingga matanya merah membara. Sang raksasa pun percaya dan larut kembali dalam kegembiraan pernikahannya.''',
        bodyEn: '''Thrym welcomed the arrival of "Freyja" with great joy and prepared a lavish feast. But the bride behaved strangely: at the banquet, Thor devoured an entire ox, eight whole salmon, all the delicacies set aside for the women, and drained three casks of mead. Thrym was astonished at his bride's appetite, but the cunning Loki quickly explained that Freyja had not eaten a thing for eight nights, so eager was she in anticipation of the wedding. When Thrym lifted the veil to kiss his bride, he recoiled at a pair of eyes blazing like fire, and drew back in fear. Once more Loki claimed that Freyja had not slept for eight nights out of burning desire, which is why her eyes glowed red. The giant believed him and sank back into the delight of his wedding.''',
      ),
      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Amukan Palu',
        headingEn: 'The Fury of the Hammer',
        body: '''Sesuai adat pernikahan raksasa, Thrym memerintahkan agar palu Mjolnir dibawa masuk dan diletakkan di pangkuan sang pengantin untuk memberkati perjanjian nikah. Begitu palu sakti itu diletakkan di pangkuannya, Thor tertawa dalam hati dan hatinya melonjak gembira. Ia menyingkap cadarnya, mencengkeram gagang Mjolnir, dan bangkit dalam wujud aslinya yang perkasa. Dengan satu ayunan, Thor menghantam Thrym hingga tewas seketika, lalu menumpas seluruh raksasa yang hadir dalam pesta itu satu per satu. Bahkan saudari tua Thrym yang tadi meminta mahar dari sang pengantin turut dihajar oleh palu, menerima "hadiah pernikahan" berupa pukulan maut alih-alih emas. Setelah membantai seluruh bangsa raksasa di aula itu, Thor pun kembali ke Asgard dengan Mjolnir di genggaman, memulihkan kehormatannya dan keamanan para dewa.''',
        bodyEn: '''As giant wedding custom required, Thrym ordered that the hammer Mjolnir be brought in and laid in the bride's lap to hallow the marriage pact. The moment the sacred hammer was placed on his lap, Thor laughed inwardly and his heart leapt with joy. He threw off his veil, gripped Mjolnir's handle, and rose in his true and mighty form. With a single swing, Thor struck Thrym dead on the spot, then crushed every giant present at the feast one by one. Even Thrym's aged sister, who had earlier begged a bridal gift, was smitten by the hammer, receiving a "wedding gift" of a deadly blow instead of gold. Having slaughtered the whole giant race in that hall, Thor returned to Asgard with Mjolnir in his grasp, restoring his honor and the safety of the gods.''',
      ),
    ],
    characters: [
      'Thor, dewa guntur yang kehilangan palu dan menyamar sebagai pengantin',
